Text.Value: If you don't know what it is, how do you have it?
I don't know how I feel about this.
Your faith is your own concern, not mine.
Agreed.
How did you come into possession of that artefact exactly?
You've got some explaining to do first - what is that thing you have?
Drop the matter.
It's nothing, I swear.
In future, I expect you to be honest. Let's leave it at that for now.
You worship Shar? Blimey. She and my beloved Mystra are not exactly friends.
Hold on - at least tell me what it is first.
Leave.
Gather your thoughts. Then perhaps we can talk some more.
*Your vision clouds, leaving you in a dark, featureless shadowscape. Nothingness in every direction.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: No cinematics until dead tribunal are designed. See state context for ongoing visual info
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: These narrator nodes are intended for medium-term use until the relevant NPCs are designed and cast. Ultimately they'll be replaced with cinematics, but the narrator nodes should be recorded and included when this dialogue is patched in,

Text.Value: Don't give me that look. I don't know what just happened any more than you do. We should keep going.
Not good enough. Explain yourself, or I'll cut you loose.
Give me the artefact. Better if I hold onto it.
True. I didn't think you'd react so pragmatically. Perhaps I should have told you sooner.
Yes, and a lot of my people died in the process. I won't fail them - not after what I saw your kind do to them.
There - you have the truth, for all it's worth. Let's continue.
Aid their search for the Prism, and you will be worthy to stand beside them. In my presence.
It's been some time since I met another faithful of Shar. Are you versed in her teachings?
I wouldn't quite say that, but it'll be safe with me. Let's go.
I don't know... not exactly. All I know is it's important I get it back to Baldur's Gate. At any cost.
There must be more to it - I need you to level with me.
My power grows. My forces gather. The reckoning draws near...

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Voice grows more distant, fading out
EditorData.SFXTags: SFX_Special - strange box pulses with energy, SFX_Special - voice fades away

Text.Value: Well, thank you for sharing.
Trust me, I will. Let's keep going.

EditorData.stateContext: Voice/visions gone. Party normal. Box is in Shadowheart's hands, not glowing.

Text.Value: I want to know about your Shar worship before we go any farther.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH's Shar worship wasn't discussed yet.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player suddenly halts as they experience a deafening ringing sound in their head. They wince in pain.

Text.Value: What's in Baldur's Gate?
Out of the question. This is my mission - I won't just give it away.
Trust me, I'll guard it with my life. Let's keep going.
I... yes, she must. I'll offer thanks to her in my prayers - and we should speak more later. Alone, ideally.
*No doubt the githyanki will seek to reclaim that which is theirs.*
Let's see how open-minded I can be then: tell me more about your Shar worship.
I can't trust you. Best if we travel separately for now.
Talk to me later. We've got more pressing matters to see to right now.
I just saved you. Keep that in mind, next time you want to air your grievances.
I know those symbols - githyanki runes. Ancient as Vlaakith herself. You stole that from my people.
No need to thank me - this is out of pure necessity - pure desperation, in fact.
The goddess of secrets? How telling.
*The three figures in the vision - the Chosen - are searching for it. With the cultists' aid, it will not be long before they find it, before they find you.
Leave.
I... I am a servant of Shar. My home is a secret cloister in Baldur's Gate. I need to bring that artefact back there, no matter what.
Keep that thing safe - seems we'll need it.

EditorData.stateContext: Party reacts with discomfort to psionic power/voice.

Text.Value: You must know something about what that thing is.
You've got some explaining to do first - why do you carry a gith relic?
Then it's your own fault for not asking.
Let's press on.
Though perhaps that might change, if you can show an open mind.

EditorData.NodeContext: Conceding jus a little towards the player's hurt feelings - but conditionally

Text.Value: That's an unusual artefact you have there, Shadowheart. A most unlikely protector...
If I reach my contact in the city, I'll have my memories restored. Until then, I have to guard the artefact with my life.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: If the player hasn't already heard about SH's memory loss.

Text.Value: Enough, both of you. We need to work together.
Who says you have to feel anything?
Just take care of it. Seems like it's as important to me as it is to you.
*Incomprehensible gith runes adorn the artefact. It lifts the pain from you, pushing the voice away.*
*You feel energy pulsing from the artefact. Lifting the pain from you. Pushing the voice away.*

EditorData.SFXTags: SFX_Special - strange box pulses with energy

Text.Value: A Shar worshipper? Not my usual quarry - nor my usual ally.
I trust you more than most, but I'm sorry - that's too much to ask. This is my responsibility.
Tell me about the artefact. What just happened?
There's nothing more I can tell you. All I remember is that I have to get back to my contact in the city.
SPEAK, OR I BREAK IT, THEN YOU.
I'll have answers, or I'll have blood.
Because it was our mission to retrieve it - me and... the others. I'm the only one who made it.

EditorData.NodeContext: hesitates and trails off at the end - about to reveal her background.

Text.Value: All we can do is try, I suppose...
*The voice is irresistible. You recognise the overwhelming authority that you've used on others, only infinitely stronger, and turned against you...*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: If the player used their illithid persuasion skills before this, the narrator notes that what they're feeling now feels like the flipside of that power they used.

Text.Value: *The voice is irresistible. Every word is drenched with a power and authority that you do not understand, but cannot deny.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The player hasn't used their illithid powers

Text.Value: I'm not sure I want to know - but it's gone now. We should keep moving.

EditorData.NodeContext: Troubled at what just happened, Eager to move past it.

Text.Value: Forget it.
I told you already, now forget it. Let's keep going.
That was far from nothing. Tell me what you know, please.
Hear my voice. Obey my command.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Characters look on the verge of collapsing.
EditorData.NodeContext: Faint, yet authoritative. The voice of a omnipotent, yet unseen being.
EditorData.SFXTags: SFX_Special - post processing on Distant Voice to have it sound faint yet authoratative. Should persist through dialogue

Text.Value: I think that was the Absolute speaking to us... but we managed to shield ourselves. We should keep moving.

EditorData.NodeContext: Troubled at what just happened, Eager to move past it.

Text.Value: *You have evaded them so far. Thanks, it seems, to the artefact itself. But how long can such protection last?*
I didn't agree to join up with a Shar worshipper.
If you insist. Don't expect to fare well without me to save you.
I bow to Shar also. The Dark Lady must favour us, to have brought us together.
Leave.
*And you still do not know what it even is.*
These are my Chosen. They speak for me.
For now. But any crimes against my kin will be answered for, in time.
Then go ahead. It won't change what I have to say to you.
Gladly.
*Shadowheart has made her position clear - she will see that it is taken to its destination. At any cost.*
If you insist. But make it quick - we have far bigger concerns.
Agreed. There's too much at stake for petty squabbles.
I knew it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Reacting to the revelation Shadowheart is a Sharran. Karlach might be a little awkwardly victorious here; this isn't the right time for her outburst.

Text.Value: *A powerful artefact indeed, to have caught the attention of so many. Not least, the Absolute itself.*
The vision... that voice - what was it?
I suppose if we're to continue together, I may as well tell you. I serve Shar. My home is a secret cloister in Baldur's Gate.
I don't know what that toy of hers is, but I'm glad it's on our side.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Voice, visions and pisonic magic fade entirely. The gith artefact is already back in SH's hands, and  has ceased glowing.
EditorData.SFXTags: SFX_Special - energy from strange box dissipates

Text.Value: Now that the truth's out, tell me more.
That power... is that what happens to others, when we use the parasite on them?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Available only if the party used tadpole powers on an absolute follower previously.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player experiences a vision of Ketheric, Gortash and Orin in a TBD environment while the voice of the Absolute continues to speak. Note: glimpses of the three presented as psionic imagery.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Cinematic node flagged impossible until cinematics can be implemented

Text.Value: I'm not sorry I kept this from you. Not one bit.
I imagine you must have questions. We should talk.
We can discuss this later. But let's just try a little more honesty going forward.
*Then, there are three figures before you. An armoured male elf, exuding power and command. A handsome younger man with a quick, easy smile. And a pale young woman with even paler eyes...*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: No cinematics until dead tribunal are designed. See state context for ongoing visual info
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: These narrator nodes are intended for medium-term use until the relevant NPCs are designed and cast. Ultimately they'll be replaced with cinematics, but the narrator nodes should be recorded and included when this dialogue is patched in,

Text.Value: Nice one, Shadowheart. That thing in your pocket seems powerful as hell.

EditorData.NodeContext: It's a serious matter, so not too cheeky

Text.Value: Why Baldur's Gate? What aren't you telling me?

EditorData.AnimationTags: [SH] Thrusts Orpheus box into frame and pushes forward through the power of the Absolute. End hooks into existing SH idle for revealing the box (SH_HasBox_Hover_SH_LOOP)
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The vision fades. The player sees the gith artefact levitating, next to Shadowheart, who has just appeared.
EditorData.SFXTags: SFX_Special - strange box pulses with energy

Text.Value: Your blindness as much as my deception, Selûnite. We can talk about this later - if you're willing.
Isn't that something? The artefact scattered the voice to the four winds.
Perhaps, but whatever it was, I don't want to experience it again.
The voice is gone - muted by this... this gith relic. Why does a half-elf carry it?
Forever, ideally. And you assume too much about what I can and cannot tell.
Secrecy is everything for Shar's children. It's our code, our creed, our shield.
And exactly what did retrieving the artefact entail?
I don't care who you worship. Tell me about that artefact.

EditorData.stateContext: Glowing gith artefact levitating near Shadowheart. Party still suffering from pisonic power of the Absolute

Text.Value: I even keep secrets from myself - I had my memories suppressed, so that nothing I knew could be used against the Dark Lady. Once I prove myself, my memories will be restored.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node only if the memory suppression beat wasn't established

Text.Value: Hold on - that artefact seemed to stop the voice. What is it?
Wait. I don't know what this thing is. All I know is that I've to get it to Baldur's Gate, at any cost. That's all I have for you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Displeased, Reluctantly sharing what she knows after being issued an ultimatum.

Text.Value: A group of us were sent to retrieve the artefact. Now I'm the only one left. I can't afford to fail.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The vision fades. The player sees that the strange box Shadowheart has is levitating before her. It's pulsing with strange, otherworldly light.
EditorData.SFXTags: SFX_Special - strange box pulses with energy

Text.Value: You've been lying to me. How long were you going to keep this secret?
Agreed.
Seems that trinket's important. Keep it close.
Heavens forbid. We're all entitled to our secrets.
I can't tell you any more. This mission required utmost secrecy - we all submitted to having our memories suppressed so that we couldn't betray Shar's confidence.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: If the player hasn't already heard about SH's memory loss.

Text.Value: Shar is an abomination. You deceived me.
Of course I am. But we can talk about this later - let's go.
My home - a cloister of Shar followers, hidden in the city.

Synopsis:
The party hears the voice of the Absolute, faint, in their minds.
Shadowheart takes out the infernal puzzle box, it glows brighter and brighter, and then the voice stops. Player avatar questions Shadowheart about the box. If the player is not aware of Shadowheart being a Shar worshipper, then they can discover this here, if she tells them about the artefact.
